eted at {{ $now.toFormat('HH:mm') }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[6453,400],"id":"416205eb-bbb4-4fe5-ab23-8536b09e0a50","name":"Send Summary to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"88c140f9-b8c5-425b-9e3e-bf9996449282","name":"failedNode","value":"={{ $json.error?.node?.name || 'unknown' }}","type":"string"},{"id":"228d9339-d5f4-4416-9495-8cfa8315cce2","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"a8edaf2a-85b2-4154-9268-46c8b4658119","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[5805,1420],"id":"cd0236b9-ab46-4f7b-9c6b-b1d3611df51b","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#social","cachedResultName":"#social"},"text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[6129,1420],"id":"6371504f-a6de-4c9f-aa75-0ed93c316502","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Hourly Schedule\n\nStarts the workflow on a timer — every 6 h. No input data; downstream nodes fetch what they need.\n\nNext: Keep Valid Posts","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"4d2eaf38-bb83-8dfe-23e4-98a7e0cd27f1","name":"Note: Hourly Schedule"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Keep Valid Posts\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Detect Sentiment","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"917b65c4-cd63-e837-9974-0e8c17534126","name":"Note: Keep Valid Posts"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Detect Sentiment\n\nScores the text's sentiment; ports fire positive / neutral / negative.\n\nPorts: ①→ Escalate Negative — Slack · ②→ Log Neutral Feedback, Capture Failure Context · ③→ Thank the Sender\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"6178b6f5-13b9-4591-9aab-508089a33102","name":"Note: Detect Sentiment"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Google Gemini Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `models/gemini-2.5-flash`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Detect Sentiment** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 Google AI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[561,1090],"id":"eb7172be-52e0-fcbb-f61a-c6f037f06533","name":"Note: Google Gemini Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Negative — Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Collect All Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,40],"id":"fcd82b44-c215-1475-a79d-d5b4ba2525b8","name":"Note: Escalate Negative — Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Log Neutral Feedback\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Collect All Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1209,520],"id":"c1a2cfae-aaa2-f736-1a5f-2eae7b2f05a3","name":"Note: Log Neutral Feedback"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Thank the Sender\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Collect All Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1533,1000],"id":"4b9813ef-ca8a-b24f-f2d0-d6666a70dd01","name":"Note: Thank the Sender"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Collect All Outcomes\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Sort Posts Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2505,520],"id":"1bb1d010-98fb-e781-c991-db6928dc0271","name":"Note: Collect All Outcomes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Posts Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3801,520],"id":"f914cc94-b50b-e748-cc8a-bfd0d13285bc","name":"Note: Sort Posts Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Stamp Processing Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4125,520],"id":"81c6d7af-7d41-decf-b708-b80c893669c2","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Processing Time\n\nStamps `processedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4449,520],"id":"fd1342ee-8de2-ad3c-ab9a-30132a19e708","name":"Note: Stamp Processing Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Tag Pipeline Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,520],"id":"3609ebfe-f37e-28b8-4544-20d999c76ab7","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Tag Pipeline Metadata\n\nShapes the item: writes `pipeline`, `version`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty content","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,520],"id":"d1ad9c97-dcf8-f370-d4a8-6bc1ae459894","name":"Note: Tag Pipeline Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty content\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5421,520],"id":"5131e6cb-5233-d81e-170a-6669f95484df","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty content"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5745,520],"id":"7c57dca2-390f-e607-cc4d-315d619fa8db","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6069,520],"id":"3613e3ed-b512-c78d-1ef5-3a99180ad13b","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6393,520],"id":"d99f83a4-3406-09e9-99b8-e62fc8d53e36","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5745,1540],"id":"ad4f2f74-bbec-dd4b-71af-dfacc3cc568e","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6069,1540],"id":"2108dd63-669d-588c-f413-e616811af7be","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Listen for brand mentions with HTTP / REST API and Slack and log the results\n\n**Pattern:** Social Listening · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nListen for brand mentions with HTTP / REST API and Slack and log the results. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual listening is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Keep Valid Posts → Detect Sentiment → Escalate Negative — Slack → Collect All Outcomes → Sort Posts Newest First → Save Execution Metadata → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to social listening without manual effort\n- Anyone automating listening in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google AI API key; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"29ac41e7-948d-a2b7-5dd4-05e0b95a4285","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-500],"id":"7e9c74d6-24ba-360f-161b-2fc45be420bc","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-500],"id":"9ebf64e5-9e57-35e0-5d9a-fbc70d1460f0","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your listening process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-500],"id":"41cbd4ee-d9eb-eacc-1512-06118ed26e05","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Hourly Schedule":{"main":[[{"node":"Keep Valid Posts","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Keep Valid Posts":{"main":[[{"node":"Detect Sentiment","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Google Gemini Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Detect Sentiment","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Detect Sentiment":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Negative — Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Log Neutral Feedback","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Thank the Sender","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Negative — Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Collect All Outcomes","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Log Neutral Feedback":{"main":[[{"node":"Collect All Outcomes","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Thank the Sender":{"main":[[{"node":"Collect All Outcomes","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Collect All Outcomes":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Posts Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Posts Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Processing Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Processing Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Tag Pipeline Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Tag Pipeline Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty content","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty content":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"ffe11884-032c-41b8-a6b8-aae8c883c9a7","id":"FDX07332"}